text.__SUMMARY__: Grevillea callichlaena is a  shrub species which is endemic to mountainous areas of eastern Victoria in Australia. The species was first formally described in 2005. The species is listed, under the name Grevillea sp. aff. miqueliana (Mount Benambra),  as "Vulnerable in Victoria" on the Victorian Department of Sustainability and Environment's Advisory List of Rare Or Threatened Plants In Victoria. It occurs on Mount Benambra in the Alpine National Park Flowering occurs predominantly between October and March in the species' native range.
